overview.eaover:
The official zoning layer for the City of San Diego, depicting current base zone designations and boundaries in the City. Updates are applied to the layer when zone designations and boundaries are changed by rezone ordinances adopted by City Council.
ZONE_NAME is the name applied to the geographic area(s) which comprise a specific type of zoning. For example, RS-17 is the zone name applied to areas where a specific type of residential zoning is in effect.
IMP_DATE is the date on which a zone change actually takes effect, or "implements."
ORDNUM is a unique alphanumeric value assigned by City Council to every new rezone ordinance. An ordinance number begins with the letter O ("ordinance"), followed by a unique five-digit number. This number increases by 1 with the issuance of each new ordinance. Following this number is the series code -- either OS ("old series") or NS ("new series"). Here is a sample ordinance number: O-19459 NS
